Sentencas: Direct utilization of olive mill wastewater sludge (OMWS) bio-oil prepared via fast pyrolysis in a Direct-Biofuel Solid Oxide Fuel Cell (DB-SOFC) was investigated.
Titulo: Exploration of Complex Electrochemical and Chemo-mechanical Behavior of Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Fueled with Pyrolysis Bio-oil

Sentencas: A viable power densities (>1,000 W m(-2) at 650 degrees C) and 6 h operation under open circuit conditions were obtained despite crude bio-oil complex chemistry.
Titulo: Exploration of Complex Electrochemical and Chemo-mechanical Behavior of Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Fueled with Pyrolysis Bio-oil

Sentencas: When heated, bio-oil decomposes yielding gases, volatiles and solid residues (biochar).
Titulo: Exploration of Complex Electrochemical and Chemo-mechanical Behavior of Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Fueled with Pyrolysis Bio-oil

Sentencas: At 650 degrees C, polarization curve and impedance spectra of SOFC fed by bio-oil showed peculiar shapes related to complex kinetics and charge transfer mechanism within the anode.
Titulo: Exploration of Complex Electrochemical and Chemo-mechanical Behavior of Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Fueled with Pyrolysis Bio-oil

Sentencas: The carbon accumulation at 650 degrees C is managed through oxidations with oxide ions and chemical reaction with CO2 and H2O gases.
Titulo: Exploration of Complex Electrochemical and Chemo-mechanical Behavior of Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Fueled with Pyrolysis Bio-oil

Sentencas: Above 700 degrees C, performance degradation was noted related to biochar accumulation at the anode though the promotion of Boudouard reaction, the increase in O2- transfer and possible carbon electrochemical oxidations.
Titulo: Exploration of Complex Electrochemical and Chemo-mechanical Behavior of Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Fueled with Pyrolysis Bio-oil

Sentencas: The anode chemo-mechanical instability was observed explaining the rise in cell ohmic resistance and performance degradation after 6 operating hours.
Titulo: Exploration of Complex Electrochemical and Chemo-mechanical Behavior of Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Fueled with Pyrolysis Bio-oil

Sentencas: Globally, this work demonstrates that direct fed SOFCs with OMWS bio-oil is achievable using Ni-SDC anode but enhancement in fuel quality and in anode catalytic activity and stability are required to improve significantly the cell performance.
Titulo: Exploration of Complex Electrochemical and Chemo-mechanical Behavior of Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Fueled with Pyrolysis Bio-oil
